Screen API documentation
=========

API
=========

DEVICE-SPECIFIC FUNCTIONS:
screen_init() - Initialise the screen.
screen_backlight_on() - Turn on the screen backlight.
screen_backlight_off() - Turn off the screen backlight.
screen_plot_pixel(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, uint16_t color) - Puts one pixel on the screen.
screen_fill(uint16_t color) - Fills the screen with one color.
screen_putchar(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, uint16_t color, int* font, char character) - Places one character on the screen.
screen_refresh() - Pushes the screen buffer to the screen.

GLOBAL FUNCTIONS:
screen_print(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, uint16_t color, int* font, const char* string) - Print a string to the screen.
screen_print_centered(uint16_t y, uint16_t color, int* font, const char* string) - Print a string to the screen, centered on the X axis.
screen_rect(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, uint16_t x2, uint16_t y2, uint16_t color) - Draw a rectangle to the screen.
screen_filled_rect(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, uint16_t x2, uint16_t y2, uint16_t color) - Draw a filled rectangle to the screen.
screen_circle(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, int16_t r, uint16_t color) - Draws a circle to the screen.
screen_filled_circle(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, int16_t r, uint16_t color) - Draws a filled circle to the screen.
screen_line(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, uint16_t x2, uint16_t y2, uint16_t color) - Draw a line on the screen.
screen_fasthline(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, uint16_t x2, uint16_t color) - Quickly (skip DDA) draw a horizontal line on the screen.
screen_fastvline(uint16_t x, uint16_t y, uint16_t y2, uint16_t color) - Quickly (skip DDA) draw a vertical line on the screen.

DEVICE-SPECIFIC DEFINES:
SCREEN_WIDTH - Screen width.
SCREEN_HEIGHT - Screen height.
SCREEN_COLOR_BLACK - Value for the color black.
SCREEN_COLOR_WHITE - Value for the color white.
SCREEN_COLOR_RED - Value for the color red.
SCREEN_COLOR_BLUE - Value for the color blue.
SCREEN_COLOR_GREEN - Value for the color green.

GLOBAL DEFINES:
SCREEN_FONT_DEFAULT - Pointer to the default font.

PORTING 
=========
All devices must provide a (or use a pre-existing) section in source/hardware/screen.c with the device-specific functions and defines above.
